We were in #Davos this week at a moment of immense consequence and uncertainty.
 
Political, geopolitical and macroeconomic landscapes all are shifting under our feet. At the very moment the clock is quickly ticking down to meet critical global priorities. Driving economic growth, reducing carbon emissions, finding ways to end conflict—all cannot wait. And the only way to make progress on these issues is by working together. But our cooperative approaches may need to adapt to a new, more uncertain, era.
We will need to be innovative and creative, and work with each other even if we don’t see eye to eye on everything.
 
Our week in Davos showed that this is possible.
 
Leaders from around the world—from the public and private sectors—with different views gathered to show how we can collaborate. And I am heartened by the impact so far.
 
I am so proud of what we have achieved together. This week is putting us on a strong course for the year ahead—a year that will have immense consequence. Because the progress we make over the coming months will not only deliver results in the near term but will shape our course for years to come.
 
I am so optimistic about what lies ahead because of how much we have already accomplished. Now we commit to continuing to find cooperative approaches ahead.
 
So that when we meet again next year, we will even further toward our goal of a more stable, sustainable and peaceful world.
 
Thank you.
 
#wef25

Obstetrician and humanitarian Jemilah Mahmood of @sunwaycph has helped people in conflict and disaster zones across the world. Climate change is already affecting the #health of the world's poorest, she says. 

By 2050, #climatechange is likely to cause an additional 14.5 million deaths and $12.5 trillion in economic losses worldwide, according to a World Economic Forum report. Tap the link in our bio to learn how #healthcare systems need to transform to meet these challenges in Quantifying the Impact of Climate Change on Human Health.

#PlanetaryHealth #Humanitarian #WomensHealth #HealthEquity
